	<td bgcolor="#F1F1F1" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ><img src="images/icons/icon12.gif" alt="Wink" border="0"> <b>Well...</b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >While I think that in many terms, how fast you deal dmg is a direct equivalent to your desirability in ideals of power. I mean, the faster you kill stuff, the better.<br>
<br>
But, you said yourself that you wanted choices...giving up this, for that.<br>
<br>
As is, you're giving up 40 percent dmg output, for less taunt. That seems like a fair trade off to me....but I'm just playing devils advocate here. Perhaps it would be a lot more fair if it was 20 percent...but I guess that's up to the masses.<br>
<br>
However, you're very right in that by limiting Paladins and Shadowknights to 1h at a time, they greatly hindered the role they play. It should be YOUR decision if you want to be a damage dealer vs. a damage taker.<br>
<br>
But, I don't think increasing the power of 2h is the answer. It merely shifts the power, when the problem is in the root, not the surface.<br>
<br>
Oh well...hopefully that made sense,<br>
Nekiah Dragonsbane</font></p>
	
