<!-- spacer --></td><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td></tr></table>
<table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor="#555576"  width="100%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#F1F1F1" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post6675"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Rezz</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Posting Neophyte</font><br>
	<p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Registered: Jul 2001<br>
	Location: <br>
	Posts: 11</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F1F1F1" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Nothing is quite as fun as swinging a 32/36 2hs and hitting for 20s... this shouldn't even happen. The damage of the weapon should be the MIN damage you do, and having higher str should increase not only the min damage, but the max damage as well. Sort of a tiered increase. Min swing is base damage of weapon, the sweetspot should be double, and the max should be 4x the base damage of the weapon. This is at 100str. As you increase your str, you should get an additional bonus to each one of these numbers, due to big, gnarly guys will swing a bat a lot harder than a 98lb weakling. Perhaps a str/100 sorta thing to multiply the base damage by.<br>
<br>
lets take the weapon I used as an example (32/36 2hs: Exquisite Velium Claidhmore)<br>
<br>
a character with 100 str would have damage along these lines:<br>
<br>
32dmg min -- 64dmg average -- 128dmg high hit<br>
<br>
a character with 75 str would have damage along these lines:<br>
<br>
24dmg min -- 48dmg average -- 96 dmg high hit<br>
<br>
a character with 150 str would have damage along these lines:<br>
<br>
48dmg min -- 96dmg average -- 192dmg high hit<br>
<br>
the idea is that weapon skill should be your skill with the weapon, not how hard you hit with it. fast weapons would still do fast damage, but holding a massive broadsword would do considerably more damage if you connect, much more than a little sword you hold in each hand per hit. Sure, you could piss off a monster more easily by inflicting many tiny wounds, but the damage would be from the guy lopping limbs off one at a time.<br>
<br>
Since the almost 2h stats of the pal/SK 1h type swords (ebon mace compared to jade mace. The ebon mace seems almost a 2h weapon ratio in damage) This would give us a little bit of an edge with the damage due to us being a heavily armed class. I also think that shields should have a lot higher AC on them, or forget AC entirely.  Perhaps each shield would actually just modify certain attributes, such as AC.  Consider this:<br>
<br>
Instead of a shield adding say, 40ish ac (using 25ac base shield for median purposes) to your stat, it would multiply your AC by 1.125<br>
<br>
800ac SK equips the shield, his AC moves up to 900ac. That's the kind of increase I see as a shield having on a tank. The shield deflects some of the str of the blow, meaning that a heavily armed tank would feel less of a hit. While this may seem like a massive increase, consider the negative that Paladins/SKs carry by not doing the massive damge of a 2hander (double 22's baby. 2hs l33t =\) To make up for this, they should gain an advantage in the defense department.<br>
<br>
Ok, now think of the seriously sick AC on some of the ToV shields. The most badass shield in the game that I can think of (55ac- dun remember the name, it's the SK one) Would confer a larger modifier to the AC of the SK/Pal while having it equipped.  1.4 modifier. Same sorry tank with 800ac, puts this shield on, and voila, 1120ac.  I view Shields as a means to either block or absorb some of the damage of an attack.   I know this probably isn't feasible with the current engine, but these are a couple ideas I've been kicking around when thinking of ways to improve paladins and shadowknights for either defense or melee purposes.<br>
<br>
Also, like Kreugen said, it gets a little monotonous to see every warrior using two weapons all the time, and the most well equipped warriors in the game having almost identical gear.  perhaps having melee specializations?  Ie, leveling the playing field on all weapon skills for all classes, but letting one skill (whichever weapon skill the player chooses at his guild) Go say, 25-50 points higher skillwise than his other weapon skills. With the ac multiplier, a warrior could hold taunt by using a 1h weapon and be able to take hits better. He wouldn't be able to match the damage of a duel wielder (duel wielding being considered a weapon skill. Ie, being able to use 2 1hs weapons wouldn't increase the skill with the weapons themselves, such as 1hs, but would increase the skill at using 2 weapons period) but he would be able to do higher damage than not, and using the best shield, a 1200ac warrior would be able to have 1680ac and still do a decent amount of damage. This makes the "tank" idea seem more than just having HPs and being able to duel wield.<br>
<br>
Having a melee specialization would also mean that it would be feasible for paladins and shadowknights to do increased damage with 2h weapons. Perhaps giving classes that choose to specialize in a 2h weapon skill a critical hit once choosing that as their specialization.  Ie, a paladin chooses to go above 225 skill, maxing at 250 or so, and is able to hit with Critical hits only when using a 2h weapon.  And so warriors don't bitch, let them trade specializations whenever they want. Their skill with the specialization they had before they changed would decrease slowly, on par with the increases in their new specialization. Other classes wouldn't have the option of changing.<br>
<br>
Just tossing out ideas <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt=""> I want to see 2h using warriors goin at the uber mobs, and the guy getting hit using a shield to keep the damage down, instead of 5 warriors armed with primal in one hand and epic in the offhand <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt=""></font></p>
	
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><br>
__________________<br>
Rezz<br>
60 Grave Lord of L`Malla<br>
Druzzil Ro</font></p>
